article.headline: Bucknell 75, Holy Cross 41
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Cameron Ayers scored 13 points and Bucknell routed Holy Cross 75-41 on Saturday night for its sixth win in a row. Bryan Cohen added 12 points, and Mike Muscala had 11 points and 11 rebounds for the Bison, who had 12 players score. Bucknell's bench outscored the Crusaders' reserves 35-5. Bucknell (15-6, 5-0 Patriot League) shot 44.6 percent (25 of 56) from the field and outrebounded he Crusaders 49-30. Holy Cross shot a season-low 24.6 percent from the field, including 2 of 14 from 3-point range, and was held to fewer than 45 points for the fourth time this season. The Bison bolted to a 30-19 halftime lead and used a 14-1 run to hold a 47-23 advantage with 12:33 to play. The lead remained more than 20 points the rest of the game. Devin Brown scored 11 points and Dave Dudzinski added 10 for the Crusaders (8-11, 2-3).
